
                              wc.sh

grab a random wallpaper from wallhaven & set it..

§ prerequisites
• jq
• curl
• feh

sudo pacman -S jq curl

§ installation
git clone https://github.com/getjared/bash.git
cd bash/wc
chmod +x wc.sh

§ usage
• ./wc
• -b (set random wallpaper)
• -nsfw (allow nsfw)
• -c (remove all walls from cache)
• -s (save current to specific place) (./wc -s /home/jared/walls)

it will save and store the images it gets into ./cache/wc/images

./wc -b       (will ignore not safe for work content)
./wc -b -nsfw (will enable not safe for work content)
